div.p:
—To complete the multilateral negotiations on mutual force reductions in
                        Central Europe, so that security will be enhanced for all the countries of
                        Europe;

—To continue the efforts to limit the spread of nuclear weapons to additional
                        countries without depriving those countries of the peaceful benefits of
                        atomic energy;

—To complete ratification of the recently negotiated treaty banning
                        underground nuclear testing by the United States and U.S.S.R. above a
                        certain threshold;

—To begin negotiations on the recently agreed effort to overcome the possible
                        dangers of environmental modification techniques for military purposes;
                        and
